Switched to the weaker Claude Sonnet 4.6. No problem.

This confirms a suspicion I've had for a while: the safety filters of major AI providers seem increasingly calibrated against offensive security topics, regardless of context.

For pentesters and red teamers, this is a real issue. You can't analyze public research, can't model threats, and end up relying on cheaper, "dumber" models because the flagship ones are too restricted.

